  "text": "2. HBeAg-negative patients ( Table 9 ) -The Phase III clinical trial which included 446 HBeAg-negative patients showed that a significantly higher percent of patients who received telbivudine had undetectable HBV DNA by PCR assay compared to those who received lamivudine: 88% versus 71% and 82% versus 57%, after 1 and 2 years of treatment, respectively. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Normalization of ALT was observed in: 74% versus 79% and 78% versus 70% after 1 and 2 years of telbivudine and lamivudine treatment, respectively.",
